areal volumes in this series is to present up-to-date information on polities, particularly those that are not well known to researchers in the field, thereby providing descriptions of language planning and policy in countries around the world. The longer range purpose of collecting comparable information on the full range of polities is to facilitate the development of a richer theory to guide language policy and planning in polities that undertake the development of national and local language policy initiatives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage planningzLatin America. 0aLanguage policyzLatin America. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aEcuador.  aMexico.  aParaguay.  alanguage planning.  alanguage policy.  alinguistic diversity.  anon-indigenous languages.1 aBaldauf Jr, Richard B, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaldauf, Richard B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGynan, Shaw N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaboud, Marleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Robert B, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaplan, Robert B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Kendall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanda, Laura Garcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Pauline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTerborg, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyt